Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "njeni" in different forms and positions, with translations in English:

1. *Njeni* roditelji su otišli na putovanje. (*Her* parents went on a trip.) 
2. Ona voli *njenog* psa više nego svoj. (She loves *her* dog more than her own.)
3. *Njenom* sinu je potreban novi bicikl. (*Her* son needs a new bike.)
4. *Njeni* prijatelji često dolaze u posetu. (*Her* friends often come to visit.)
5. Ja sam kupio *njen* poklon za rođendan. (I bought *her* a gift for her birthday.)
6. *Njena* kosa je tako meka i svilenkasta. (*Her* hair is so soft and silky.)
7. *Njeni* planovi su se promenili u poslednjem trenutku. (*Her* plans changed at the last minute.)
8. Molim te, donesi mi *njenu* torbu sa stola. (Please bring me *her* bag from the table.)
9. *Njenim* očima sam videla sve lepote sveta. (*Through her* eyes, I saw all the beauties of the world.)
10. *Njenih* ruku dodir je tako nežan i topao. (*Her* touch is so gentle and warm.)

I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions.